"{\"uid\": \"gbnews.com-sport-other-sport-imane-khelif-gender-test-2028-olympics\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Labour-run council shoots down claim migrant cultures 'do not respect women' ByJack Otway, Published: 05/02/2026 The boxer won gold in France back in 2024 in controversial circumstances Algerian boxer Imane Khelif has indicated willingness to undergo sex verification testing if compliance represents the final barrier to participation at the 2028 Los Angeles Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 378, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 85, \"end\": 90, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Otway_National_Park\", \"score\": 0.9999265622564366, \"rank\": 7.30212303545423e-05, \"text\": \"Otway\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Otway_National_Park\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Otway_National_Park\"}, {\"begin\": 138, \"end\": 144, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.6566759292721448, \"rank\": 0.5072070191450753, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}, {\"begin\": 190, \"end\": 198, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.9999798133331108, \"rank\": 1.649005374312367e-05, \"text\": \"Algerian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}, {\"begin\": 205, \"end\": 217, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421621021, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Labour-run council shoots\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 25}, {\"ngram\": \"migrant cultures\", \"from\": 37, \"to\": 53}, {\"ngram\": \"The boxer\", \"from\": 113, \"to\": 122}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 127, \"to\": 131}, {\"ngram\": \"controversial circumstances\", \"from\": 158, \"to\": 185}, {\"ngram\": \"willingness\", \"from\": 228, \"to\": 239}, {\"ngram\": \"sex verification testing\", \"from\": 251, \"to\": 275}, {\"ngram\": \"compliance\", \"from\": 279, \"to\": 289}, {\"ngram\": \"the final barrier\", \"from\": 301, \"to\": 318}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2028 Los Angeles Olympic Games\", \"from\": 339, \"to\": 373}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Khelif, champion of the women's welterweight division at the Paris 2024 Summer Olympics, has remained at the centre of a prolonged and increasingly politicised debate surrounding gender eligibility in elite boxing.\", \"from\": 380, \"to\": 594, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Khelif\", \"from\": 380, \"to\": 386}, {\"ngram\": \"champion\", \"from\": 388, \"to\": 396}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's welterweight division\", \"from\": 400, \"to\": 433}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris\", \"from\": 437, \"to\": 446}, {\"ngram\": \"Summer Olympics\", \"from\": 452, \"to\": 467}, {\"ngram\": \"the centre\", \"from\": 485, \"to\": 495}, {\"ngram\": \"a prolonged and increasingly politicised debate\", \"from\": 499, \"to\": 546}, {\"ngram\": \"gender eligibility\", \"from\": 559, \"to\": 577}, {\"ngram\": \"elite boxing\", \"from\": 581, \"to\": 593}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Scrutiny intensified following disqualification from the 2023 World Championships alongside Taiwanese fighter Lin Yu-ting, after the International Boxing Association cited alleged failures in eligibility testing procedures.The International Boxing Association lost international standing shortly afterwards, following a decision by the International Olympic Committee to remove official recognition amid governance and integrity concerns.TRENDINGStoriesVideosYour SayClearance to compete in Paris followed under Olympic eligibility criteria, allowing Khelif to proceed to gold without restriction.In an interview with CNN, Khelif stated acceptance of any testing framework administered by the Olympic authorities, emphasising transparency and eligibility compliance as priorities for continued competition at the highest level.Algerian boxer Imane Khelif has indicated willingness to undergo sex verification testing if compliance represents the final barrier to participation at the 2028 Los Angeles Olympic Games|GETTYThe Algerian fighter stressed the importance of safeguarding women's sport while cautioning against collateral harm inflicted on female athletes caught in regulatory crossfire.Khelif has consistently competed within women's divisions throughout an international career and has rejected attempts to recast personal circumstances as political symbolism.LATEST SPORTS NEWS:Newcastle fans demand Eddie Howe sacked after Man City thrashing in Carabao CupDeontay Wilder and Simon Jordan nearly come to blows after Tyson Fury question as boxer walks out of studioFootballer, 22, dies following three weeks coma after being hit by stray bullet during celebrationsImane Khelif was permitted to compete at the Paris Olympics by the IOC due to their gender eligibility rules |Imane KhelifAppeals were made for privacy, dignity and separation from ideological disputes dominating public discourse.The controversy gained further traction following remarks from Donald Trump, delivered during the signing of an executive order barring transgender women from female sporting categories.Public references to Khelif during that period intensified global attention and amplified online hostility.Governance of international boxing entered a transitional phase in February 2025, when World Boxing received provisional Olympic recognition.Imane Khelif won gold at the Paris Olympics in 2024|GETTYMandatory genetic testing protocols were introduced soon after, designed to establish sex at birth for eligibility purposes.Initial communications referenced Khelif by name, prompting a formal apology from World Boxing following widespread criticism.Legal challenge followed.\", \"from\": 596, \"to\": 3267, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 688, \"end\": 697, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_Taipei\", \"score\": 0.9999872391795381, \"rank\": 9.514067046566521e-06, \"text\": \"Taiwanese\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_Taipei\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_Taipei\"}, {\"begin\": 706, \"end\": 717, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lin Yu-ting\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\"}, {\"begin\": 729, \"end\": 761, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9376478575373735e-22, \"text\": \"International Boxing Association\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 823, \"end\": 855, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9376478575373735e-22, \"text\": \"International Boxing Association\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 932, \"end\": 963, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympi